A COP has been sentenced 20 years in jail for killing and robbing another policeman. The sentence was handed down today, Thursday, 17 February by Pietermaritzburg High Court. Ndumiso Memela (26) robbed and killed Sergeant Thembinkosi Buthelezi on 21 September, 2018. The statement read: “Buthelezi, who was stationed at Kokstad K9 unit was fatally shot and robbed of his service pistol while off duty in Imbali township. A case of murder was reported at Plessislaer Police Station and the case docket was allocated to Hawks members from Pietermaritzburg for thorough investigation. “ Buthelezi’s service pistol was found in Mamela’s vehicle in the Inanda area the next day. Mamela claimed he was hijacked the previous day, but was eventually arrested in the Copsville area in January 2020 and charged for murder and armed robbery. Mamela appeared in court several times up until his sentencing yesterday. He was sentenced 20 years for murder and 15 years for robbery. His sentences will run concurrently.